282
00:16:01,270 --> 00:16:03,000
Since things have come to this,

283
00:16:03,710 --> 00:16:04,910
we should plan ahead.

284
00:16:15,150 --> 00:16:15,960
At this point,

285
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:18,290
there are only two ways to survive:

286
00:16:19,710 --> 00:16:21,170
either resign from office

287
00:16:22,150 --> 00:16:22,840
or

288
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:25,410
pledge allegiance to Prince Duan.

289
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:27,410
But from the looks of it,

290
00:16:28,030 --> 00:16:29,560
you don't seem like the type

291
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:32,300
to pledge allegiance to Prince Duan.

292
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:32,960
Of course.

293
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,240
I will never pledge allegiance.

294
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:35,340
I'd rather spill my blood in the main hall

295
00:16:35,340 --> 00:16:36,600
and go down in history.

296
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:37,320
True.

297
00:16:38,390 --> 00:16:39,720
I'm planning to resign.

298
00:16:41,030 --> 00:16:42,030
Now there's no one left in the court

299
00:16:42,030 --> 00:16:43,810
worth my loyalty.

300
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:45,470
I might as well

301
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:48,440
return home and take care of my parents.

302
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:53,840
I'd actually like to
try pledging allegiance.

303
00:16:54,790 --> 00:16:55,320
Er Lan.

304
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:57,050
Now is not the time for jokes.

305
00:16:57,050 --> 00:16:58,290
I'm not joking.

306
00:16:59,030 --> 00:17:00,290
With His Majesty dead,

307
00:17:00,790 --> 00:17:03,850
most royalists will choose to resign
to stay alive.

308
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:06,240
There will be many vacancies in the court,

309
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:08,160
and Prince Duan will need people
to work for him.

310
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,290
So in the short term,

311
00:17:09,349 --> 00:17:11,680
he probably won't touch those who remain.

312
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:14,900
Er, you're smarter than this.

313
00:17:15,349 --> 00:17:16,810
Even if he doesn't act now,

314
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,160
how can we be sure Prince Duan
won't settle scores later?

315
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:20,880
Let's take it one step at a time.

316
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:22,200
When that time really comes,

317
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,800
dying then won't be too late.

318
00:17:25,589 --> 00:17:28,040
Compared to dying in a show of loyalty,

319
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:30,310
I think

320
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:32,550
His Majesty would perhaps prefer to see

321
00:17:32,550 --> 00:17:34,120
us keeping the people safe

322
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:36,350
and not letting them
suffer from the turmoil.

323
00:17:36,350 --> 00:17:38,210
Er, there's no need to insinuate.

324
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:39,830
I am now

325
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:42,830
no longer the hothead I was
when I first joined the court.

326
00:17:42,830 --> 00:17:45,560
Of course I understand
your good intentions, Er.

327
00:17:46,510 --> 00:17:47,310
It's just that

328
00:17:48,550 --> 00:17:49,610
at a time like this,

329
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,960
pledging allegiance to
someone like Prince Duan

330
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,490
and bowing my head to him...

331
00:17:54,510 --> 00:17:56,480
It would truly be a humiliation
beyond measure.

332
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:58,310
As the saying goes,
when a mansion is about to collapse,

333
00:17:58,310 --> 00:18:00,770
the power of one person
is so insignificant.

334
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,240
Life is short,

335
00:18:04,070 --> 00:18:06,270
and Er, you are in the prime of your life.

336
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:09,170
Why not live for yourself for once?

337
00:18:20,790 --> 00:18:22,310
Cen, there's something you don't know.

338
00:18:22,310 --> 00:18:23,240
I'm staying

339
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:25,540
not only for the greater good,

340
00:18:26,510 --> 00:18:28,310
but also for personal feelings.

341
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:37,800
Wait a minute.

342
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:42,440
Personal feelings?

343
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:49,330
Which lady is it?

344
00:18:49,530 --> 00:18:50,720
Have we met her?

345
00:18:51,350 --> 00:18:52,310
It's his private matter.

346
00:18:52,310 --> 00:18:53,370
Why are you prying?

347
00:18:53,830 --> 00:18:55,230
But Er isn't an outsider.

348
00:18:55,750 --> 00:18:56,150
Right.

349
00:18:56,550 --> 00:18:58,400
Right, he... He isn't an outsider.

350
00:18:58,400 --> 00:18:59,000
Indeed, he isn't an outsider.

351
00:18:59,000 --> 00:18:59,790
Since he isn't an outsider,

352
00:18:59,790 --> 00:19:01,310
then let's not leave either.

353
00:19:01,310 --> 00:19:02,960
We can't let her be alone in the court,

354
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:04,240
fighting a lone battle, right?

355
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:05,400
Didn't you just say you'd rather

356
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:07,830
spill your blood in the main hall
and go down in history?

357
00:19:07,830 --> 00:19:09,960
Why did you change your stance so fast?

358
00:19:10,870 --> 00:19:12,400
I never changed, okay? I...

359
00:19:12,590 --> 00:19:14,830
I do want to spill my blood
in the main hall.

360
00:19:14,830 --> 00:19:16,830
But since I want to spill my blood there,

361
00:19:16,830 --> 00:19:18,440
I have to get to the main hall first,
right?

362
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:19,750
I can't spill my blood at...

363
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:20,480
At the entrance, right?

364
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:21,640
You... Wait a second.

365
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:22,920
W-What about me?

366
00:19:23,070 --> 00:19:24,940
How dare you, Yang Duojie?

367
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:26,360
A-At a time like this,

368
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,730
everyone is sad.

369
00:19:29,310 --> 00:19:31,440
What about me? Don't say another word.

370
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:36,780
I originally wanted this fish...

371
00:20:01,550 --> 00:20:04,350
Actually, it would be safer for you
to stay in Peiyang to hold the fort.

372
00:20:04,350 --> 00:20:06,200
After the turmoil in the city
settles down...

373
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:07,350
Don't even think about it.

374
00:20:07,350 --> 00:20:09,680
I won't let you have your way
a second time.

375
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:12,680
Don't you want

376
00:20:12,830 --> 00:20:14,030
to travel the world anymore?

377
00:20:14,030 --> 00:20:14,720
I do.

378
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:17,350
The world is right there.

379
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:19,350
It doesn't matter if I go a bit later.

380
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:23,540
Come to think of it,

381
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:27,400
we've only known each other
for a little over half a year,

382
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,000
yet so much has happened.

383
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:32,980
We've practically

384
00:20:33,030 --> 00:20:35,160
gone through life and death together.

385
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:35,860
However,

386
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:38,070
in a sense,

387
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,860
it seems like we've only just met?

388
00:20:41,590 --> 00:20:42,030
Yeah.

389
00:20:43,550 --> 00:20:45,880
After all, you don't even know
my name yet.

390
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:49,300
I had my own worries back then,

391
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:52,530
so I didn't dare to discuss this topic
with you in detail.

392
00:20:52,790 --> 00:20:54,190
So what is your real name?

393
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:55,650
My name is...

394
00:21:03,210 --> 00:21:05,550
Don't you think the name Yu Wanyin
sounds really nice?

395
00:21:05,550 --> 00:21:07,110
I do think Yu Wanyin sounds very nice.

396
00:21:07,110 --> 00:21:08,510
So what is your real name?

397
00:21:09,110 --> 00:21:09,370
I...

398
00:21:09,620 --> 00:21:10,860
I can tell you,

399
00:21:11,350 --> 00:21:13,350
but you have to promise me one thing.

400
00:21:13,350 --> 00:21:13,950
What is it?

401
00:21:15,130 --> 00:21:16,930
You can't laugh after I tell you.

402
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:21,030
Why would I laugh?

403
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:23,650
Could it be funnier than Zhang San?

404
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:26,170
Wang Cuihua.

405
00:21:36,110 --> 00:21:36,680
For real?

406
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:42,560
Your real name is Wang Cuihua?

407
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:46,620
Wang Cuihua...

408
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:50,210
"Cuihua,

409
00:21:50,790 --> 00:21:52,390
serve the pickled cabbage!"

410
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:55,750
My third great-uncle gave me that name.

411
00:21:55,750 --> 00:21:57,350
So now you know why I hate him.

412
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:00,950
Your third great-uncle
sure had a knack for names.

413
00:22:03,790 --> 00:22:04,680
Wang Cuihua...

414
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:07,920
No wonder you put off mentioning it.

415
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:10,640
I'll get angry if you keep laughing.

416
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:11,680
Alright, alright.

417
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:12,810
I'll stop laughing.

418
00:22:16,790 --> 00:22:17,830
It seems the two of us

419
00:22:17,830 --> 00:22:19,530
are pretty evenly matched—

420
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,080
hard to tell who wins.

421
00:22:22,240 --> 00:22:24,640
I don't even mind
you're a middle schooler.

422
00:22:24,750 --> 00:22:27,150
I'm technically robbing the cradle, okay?

423
00:22:27,690 --> 00:22:29,690
What do you mean robbing the cradle?

424
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:32,310
Yes, I was a middle schooler
when I transmigrated here,

425
00:22:32,310 --> 00:22:34,110
but I've spent over 10 years in this book.

426
00:22:34,110 --> 00:22:36,070
We didn't transmigrate at the same time
after all.

427
00:22:36,070 --> 00:22:37,440
Which year did you come from?

428
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:38,000
2016.

429
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:39,720
I'm from the year 2025.

430
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:40,000
See?

431
00:22:43,110 --> 00:22:44,400
No wonder.

432
00:22:45,590 --> 00:22:47,130
When we chatted before,

433
00:22:47,270 --> 00:22:49,000
all your jokes were so old-fashioned,

434
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:49,480
like

435
00:22:50,240 --> 00:22:51,640
"blue skinny mushroom,"

436
00:22:51,720 --> 00:22:53,550
and "Yuanfang, what do you think?"

437
00:22:53,550 --> 00:22:55,480
I felt something was off back then.

438
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,930
Since we're on the subject,

439
00:23:00,350 --> 00:23:01,880
I want to ask you something.

440
00:23:03,310 --> 00:23:05,510
What is the "smell of work"?

441
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:07,760
And that saying

442
00:23:07,830 --> 00:23:09,350
"city or not"—

443
00:23:09,830 --> 00:23:10,830
what does it mean?

444
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:14,000
And that thing you always say—

445
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,460
"Zize"—what does it mean?

446
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:18,170
Want to know?

447
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,400
Then repeat after me.

448
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:22,440
Tell me wh-what it means first.

449
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:24,110
J-Just repeat after me first.

450
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:26,020
Fine. Teach me.

451
00:23:28,310 --> 00:23:28,790
Zize.

452
00:23:30,550 --> 00:23:31,030
Zize.

453
00:23:32,750 --> 00:23:33,640
Zize.

454
00:23:35,240 --> 00:23:36,050
Zize.

455
00:23:37,590 --> 00:23:38,590
What does it mean?

456
00:23:39,030 --> 00:23:42,290
It just sounds similar to "jiejie,"
meaning older sister.

457
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:43,910
Got it?

458
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:45,680
Then what about those other things,

459
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:47,070
like "laying low"
and "winner winner, chicken dinner"?

460
00:23:47,070 --> 00:23:48,590
You don't know those either?

461
00:23:48,590 --> 00:23:49,060
I don't.

462
00:23:49,350 --> 00:23:51,610
Then why did you lay low with me
last time?

463
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:53,720
I saw you were so fired up,

464
00:23:53,790 --> 00:23:56,190
so I didn't have the heart
to interrupt you.

465
00:23:56,590 --> 00:23:57,480
Little brat.

466
00:23:58,240 --> 00:24:00,370
And that... What's it called again...

467
00:24:00,590 --> 00:24:01,810
OOC?

468
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:02,630
And that

469
00:24:03,750 --> 00:24:05,530
"attention seeker"—

470
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:06,680
what does it mean?

471
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:08,540
I'll tell you what that one means.

472
00:24:08,950 --> 00:24:11,480
You're the definition of
an attention seeker.

473
00:24:11,480 --> 00:24:12,880
I'm the definition of an attention seeker?

474
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:14,000
You're an attention seeker.

475
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:14,550
Remember?

476
00:24:14,550 --> 00:24:15,400
I'm an attention seeker.

477
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:16,660
T-Then what about you?

478
00:24:38,510 --> 00:24:38,960
Cen.

479
00:24:39,110 --> 00:24:39,810
Sorry.

480
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:40,920
Why are you awake?

481
00:24:41,270 --> 00:24:42,330
Sorry I woke you up.

482
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:51,720
Physician Xiao's medicine worked.

483
00:24:52,270 --> 00:24:53,720
You look much better.

484
00:24:56,110 --> 00:24:56,750
I want to,

485
00:24:57,480 --> 00:24:58,480
while I still can,

486
00:24:59,070 --> 00:25:00,550
make a trip back to my courtyard

487
00:25:00,550 --> 00:25:02,010
and check on my Yan millet.

488
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:05,240
But right now,

489
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:06,790
it's snowing heavily outside.

490
00:25:06,790 --> 00:25:08,120
With your condition...

491
00:25:09,350 --> 00:25:10,350
If I don't go now,

492
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:16,640
I'm afraid I won't have another chance.

493
00:25:40,730 --> 00:25:41,160
I...

494
00:25:42,310 --> 00:25:42,590
I...

495
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:45,440
I'll go with you.

496
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:47,400
Okay.

497
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,720
If everything goes well,

498
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:05,980
by this time tomorrow,

499
00:26:06,350 --> 00:26:07,880
we'll have a bed to sleep in.

500
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:11,040
We'll send someone
to bring Mr. Bei back later.

501
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:13,010
Now that Bai is here too,

502
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:15,400
our hotpot for four can reopen.

503
00:26:23,270 --> 00:26:23,870
By the way.

504
00:26:24,510 --> 00:26:26,480
that Xiao Tiancai is still in the palace.

505
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:27,400
Before I left,

506
00:26:28,110 --> 00:26:30,400
I suggested the idea of
fighting poison with poison to him,

507
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:31,930
and he said it was feasible.

508
00:26:32,110 --> 00:26:33,340
Maybe by now,

509
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:35,980
he's already made a breakthrough
in his research.

510
00:26:35,980 --> 00:26:38,190
♪ A letter, a line of words ♪

511
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:39,730
♪ Picking up the pen again and again ♪

512
00:26:40,060 --> 00:26:42,200
♪ A cup of tea, a glass of wine ♪

513
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:42,580
I almost forgot about those scholars.

514
00:26:42,580 --> 00:26:43,900
♪ Drinking alone, hard to get drunk ♪

515
00:26:43,480 --> 00:26:44,750
Prince Duan won't give them a hard time,
will he?

516
00:26:43,990 --> 00:26:46,350
♪ Words unspoken ♪

517
00:26:45,590 --> 00:26:47,320
Er Lan and Yang Duojie are fine,

518
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:49,080
but I'm really worried about Li Yunxi.

519
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:50,400
♪ Shyness unhidden ♪

520
00:26:49,510 --> 00:26:51,480
He risks his life to remonstrate
at every turn.

521
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:52,390
If that happens,

522
00:26:52,050 --> 00:26:54,230
♪ Walking down a street together ♪

523
00:26:52,510 --> 00:26:53,590
and he risks his life
to remonstrate again,

524
00:26:53,590 --> 00:26:54,410
Prince Duan will...

525
00:26:54,410 --> 00:26:55,550
♪ Shoulder to shoulder ♪

526
00:26:55,910 --> 00:26:57,960
♪ Raising my head, lowering my eyes ♪

527
00:26:57,550 --> 00:26:58,410
Don't worry, Wanyin.

528
00:26:58,410 --> 00:26:59,790
♪ Blushing slightly ♪

529
00:26:59,550 --> 00:27:00,200
Everything will go well.

530
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:02,380
♪ A face flushed red at first sight ♪

531
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:02,500
I'm here.

532
00:27:03,990 --> 00:27:07,290
♪ A smile like a flower in my heart ♪

533
00:27:07,890 --> 00:27:11,270
♪ Whose longing lingers day and night? ♪

534
00:27:11,970 --> 00:27:14,980
♪ Piling up stories
and countless thoughts ♪

535
00:27:15,470 --> 00:27:17,300
♪ Walking through once, taking a glance ♪

536
00:27:15,920 --> 00:27:16,850
I believe in you.

537
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:19,230
♪ All lingering and wandering ♪

538
00:27:19,460 --> 00:27:21,200
♪ How many rains, how many winds? ♪

539
00:27:21,410 --> 00:27:23,520
♪ Looking back, it's all like smoke ♪

540
00:27:24,010 --> 00:27:27,080
♪ Watching the hazy world ♪

541
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:30,340
♪ Who still guards that yearning? ♪

542
00:27:30,460 --> 00:27:31,550
♪ Still unchanged ♪

543
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:34,900
♪ Even if months and years
pass in a blink ♪

544
00:27:35,490 --> 00:27:36,950
♪ One thought for a lifetime ♪

545
00:27:37,070 --> 00:27:44,320
♪ Waiting for someone to appear ♪

546
00:27:55,900 --> 00:27:59,460
♪ Whose longing lingers day and night? ♪

547
00:28:08,550 --> 00:28:10,210
What have the plants ever done

548
00:28:13,590 --> 00:28:15,050
to deserve such disaster?

549
00:28:16,270 --> 00:28:19,310
Fortunately, the spring breeze
will bring them back to life.

550
00:28:19,310 --> 00:28:21,110
Cen, you needn't lament so much.

551
00:28:22,070 --> 00:28:22,880
Yeah.

552
00:28:24,310 --> 00:28:25,640
When I was born,

553
00:28:26,350 --> 00:28:29,010
I was already afflicted with
a serious illness.

554
00:28:29,880 --> 00:28:32,110
I knew I wouldn't live long.

555
00:28:40,830 --> 00:28:42,200
Yet, I've always admired how plants,

556
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:43,730
though seemingly fragile,

557
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:46,780
are actually full of resilience.

558
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:50,110
Compared to humans' mere few decades
of lifespan,

559
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:53,320
plants can return to life
season after season.

560
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,490
As long as there's wind,

561
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:56,350
rain,

562
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:57,920
and soil,

563
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:00,160
they can grow freely

564
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:02,110
and joyfully.

565
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:04,940
But humans are not plants—

566
00:29:05,030 --> 00:29:06,690
how could we live in solitude?

567
00:29:07,070 --> 00:29:08,000
Cen,

568
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:10,410
you've grown close to us after all.

569
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:15,900
If it weren't for you guys
dragging me along,

570
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:18,270
not minding my coldness and frailty,

571
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:21,690
not looking down on
my dullness and awkwardness,

572
00:29:22,350 --> 00:29:23,750
I truly wouldn't know

573
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:27,000
what I've missed all these years.

574
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:35,640
Er Lan,

575
00:29:36,790 --> 00:29:37,830
did you know

576
00:29:38,400 --> 00:29:39,240
that Li

577
00:29:39,830 --> 00:29:41,440
used to look down on you?

578
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:42,550
But now,

579
00:29:43,790 --> 00:29:45,250
he's sincerely convinced

580
00:29:45,750 --> 00:29:47,750
and holds you in the highest regard.

581
00:29:48,110 --> 00:29:50,490
And for a long time,
Yang had quite a few complaints

582
00:29:50,490 --> 00:29:53,050
about the fortune-teller position
at the Imperial Astronomer,

583
00:29:53,050 --> 00:29:54,640
and he often came to me to vent.

584
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:55,070
Also,

585
00:29:55,590 --> 00:29:57,310
before Wang Zhao went on his mission,

586
00:29:57,310 --> 00:29:58,710
he asked me to take care of

587
00:29:58,790 --> 00:30:00,880
a lady selling tofu in the East Alley.

588
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:03,510
That's a secret

589
00:30:05,590 --> 00:30:07,990
he'll never have the chance
to say out loud.

590
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:16,570
Since it's a secret,

591
00:30:18,310 --> 00:30:19,480
why are you

592
00:30:20,050 --> 00:30:21,450
telling me about it, Cen?

593
00:30:24,590 --> 00:30:25,960
I'll be counting on you,

594
00:30:30,350 --> 00:30:33,210
Er Lan, to take care of these old friends
from now on.

595
00:30:45,440 --> 00:30:46,000
Okay.

596
00:30:50,070 --> 00:30:51,200
You have my promise.

597
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:53,240
Then, Cen,

598
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:57,750
would you like to hear my secret?

599
00:30:59,750 --> 00:31:01,640
For a secret to be a secret,

600
00:31:03,790 --> 00:31:06,190
it's best if the other person
doesn't know.

601
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:16,940
If humans were like plants

602
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:20,200
and had an afterlife,

603
00:31:23,440 --> 00:31:24,570
would you then, Cen?

604
00:31:30,510 --> 00:31:31,770
If there is a next life,

605
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:35,720
I'd definitely play the zither,

606
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:37,030
brew wine,

607
00:31:40,030 --> 00:31:41,690
and listen attentively to it.

608
00:32:42,690 --> 00:32:45,650
[Luo]

609
00:32:51,490 --> 00:32:53,270
[You]

610
00:32:57,830 --> 00:33:00,820
[Hai]

611
00:33:07,230 --> 00:33:11,350
[You]

612
00:33:14,380 --> 00:33:16,070
[Luo]

613
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:17,480
[Hai]

614
00:33:24,270 --> 00:33:25,900
[Capital of Xia]

615
00:33:35,270 --> 00:33:36,000
General Luo,

616
00:33:36,310 --> 00:33:37,400
Deputy General Lin,

617
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:38,480
Deputy General Zhou.

618
00:33:38,480 --> 00:33:39,960
Long time no see.

619
00:33:40,790 --> 00:33:41,400
Lord Jia.

620
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:44,370
We've been waiting here for half a day.

621
00:33:44,530 --> 00:33:46,640
Why haven't the soldiers been allowed
into the city yet?

622
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:47,100
Indeed.

623
00:33:47,790 --> 00:33:50,510
We came at urgent summons,
traveling day and night.

624
00:33:50,510 --> 00:33:52,170
But judging by the situation,

625
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:53,730
it seems no one's in a hurry.

626
00:33:54,030 --> 00:33:55,510
You jest, Generals.

627
00:33:55,750 --> 00:33:58,510
His Highness indeed
has important matters to discuss,

628
00:33:58,510 --> 00:34:00,660
so he sent us here to receive you.

629
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:01,960
That's right.

630
00:34:02,070 --> 00:34:02,720
Generals,

631
00:34:03,270 --> 00:34:06,230
please follow me
and enter the city alone first.

632
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:07,520
Just us?

633
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:09,000
What about the main troops?

634
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:09,659
Never mind.

635
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:12,800
Since this is His Highness's order,

636
00:34:12,800 --> 00:34:14,300
we shall obey.

637
00:34:15,230 --> 00:34:16,630
Li Zhong! You stay.

638
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:17,760
-Yang Yi!
-Yes!

639
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:19,000
Take a squad and come with me.

640
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:20,130
The rest, stand by!

641
00:34:28,760 --> 00:34:29,909
Please, generals,

642
00:34:30,030 --> 00:34:31,489
kindly remove your swords

643
00:34:31,630 --> 00:34:32,840
before entering the city.

644
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:33,770
What do you mean?

645
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:35,290
We led the armies

646
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:37,060
all the way here to help.

647
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:39,670
Is this the courtesy
His Highness Prince Duan shows us?

648
00:34:39,670 --> 00:34:41,400
Generals, please don't
take this the wrong way.

649
00:34:41,400 --> 00:34:42,280
It's just that

650
00:34:42,550 --> 00:34:44,110
the situation inside the city

651
00:34:44,110 --> 00:34:45,370
is delicate right now,

652
00:34:45,710 --> 00:34:47,510
with spies from all sides mingling.

653
00:34:47,510 --> 00:34:48,710
Removing your swords

654
00:34:49,440 --> 00:34:51,230
is merely a formality.

655
00:34:51,280 --> 00:34:52,230
Yes, indeed.

656
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:55,730
His Highness has prepared
a grand feast in the city,

657
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:58,620
waiting to welcome you generals

658
00:34:58,800 --> 00:35:00,400
and reward the Three Armies.

659
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:03,450
You lot

660
00:35:03,800 --> 00:35:05,070
are so twisted

661
00:35:05,480 --> 00:35:06,480
and troublesome.

662
00:35:08,860 --> 00:35:10,260
I have nothing to hide.

663
00:35:10,550 --> 00:35:11,810
If you want the swords,

664
00:35:12,030 --> 00:35:12,800
take them.

665
00:35:38,760 --> 00:35:39,490
You stay here

666
00:35:39,640 --> 00:35:41,570
and keep an eye on the Three Armies.

667
00:35:45,510 --> 00:35:48,360
Didn't Prince Duan himself
summon the Three Armies?

668
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:50,820
Why won't he let the soldiers
enter the city?

669
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:57,150
He is

670
00:35:57,510 --> 00:35:58,840
extremely suspicious.

671
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:00,300
Could it be that

672
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:04,940
there's some rift
between him and the soldiers?

673
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:06,760
But what kind of rift could it be?

674
00:36:18,660 --> 00:36:23,900
[Memorial Tablet of Emperor Xiaohewen
of Great Xia]

675
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:27,780
Your Highness.

676
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:30,150
This man

677
00:36:32,550 --> 00:36:34,680
was sent by the Central Army back then,

678
00:36:35,710 --> 00:36:36,550
right?

679
00:36:37,230 --> 00:36:38,030
That's right,

680
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:39,300
Your Highness.

681
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:40,780
They also said

682
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:42,930
General Luo's trusted aide

683
00:36:43,230 --> 00:36:44,960
interrogated him personally.

684
00:36:46,190 --> 00:36:48,590
They sent me an imposter.

685
00:36:52,090 --> 00:36:53,440
How amusing.

686
00:36:54,550 --> 00:36:55,680
This man's disguise

687
00:36:56,150 --> 00:36:57,630
was flawless.

688
00:36:59,110 --> 00:37:00,490
Perhaps General Luo,

689
00:37:00,630 --> 00:37:01,680
like us,

690
00:37:01,840 --> 00:37:03,510
was kept completely in the dark?

691
00:37:03,510 --> 00:37:04,520
The Three Armies

692
00:37:05,190 --> 00:37:07,000
have always been
under Your Highness's command.

693
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:07,280
And

694
00:37:07,510 --> 00:37:08,360
General Luo

695
00:37:09,030 --> 00:37:11,240
has technically been through
life and death with you.

696
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:12,710
He shouldn't have acted like that, right?

697
00:37:12,710 --> 00:37:15,240
If there were so many "shoulds"
in this world,

698
00:37:18,190 --> 00:37:20,470
Xiahou Dan should've long been dead!

699
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:22,050
Yes, Your Highness.

700
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:35,780
What do the craftsmen say?

701
00:37:38,070 --> 00:37:39,330
Can they replicate it?

702
00:37:39,920 --> 00:37:40,800
This object

703
00:37:41,030 --> 00:37:43,230
is designed with exquisite ingenuity.

704
00:37:43,510 --> 00:37:45,970
If we want to produce it
in large quantities,

705
00:37:46,030 --> 00:37:47,560
it'll still take some time.

706
00:37:58,760 --> 00:37:59,620
Your Highness,

707
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:01,200
please be extra careful.

708
00:38:01,230 --> 00:38:02,920
This object is very dangerous.

709
00:38:02,920 --> 00:38:04,230
Don't let it hurt you.

710
00:38:05,580 --> 00:38:07,270
There's only one bullet left.

711
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:10,570
Minister Wu.

712
00:38:11,510 --> 00:38:11,900
Yes.

713
00:38:12,670 --> 00:38:13,710
Take a guess—

714
00:38:15,110 --> 00:38:17,110
whose body will it pierce?

715
00:38:18,030 --> 00:38:19,030
Your Highness...

716
00:38:32,510 --> 00:38:33,370
Take them away.

717
00:38:36,550 --> 00:38:37,480
What's going on?

718
00:38:41,030 --> 00:38:43,480
The Imperial Guards are searching
the Three Armies one by one.

719
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:45,830
I saw that they've selected some people

720
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:47,670
from both the Left and Central Armies.
They seem to be

721
00:38:47,670 --> 00:38:51,130
-searching for suspicious individuals.
-Take this one away.

722
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:52,840
You've got sharp eyes.

723
00:38:52,840 --> 00:38:53,590
Hurry up and check

724
00:38:53,590 --> 00:38:55,440
what criteria they are using
to select people.

725
00:38:55,440 --> 00:38:55,970
This one.

726
00:38:56,030 --> 00:38:56,830
Take him away.

727
00:38:57,280 --> 00:38:58,790
They seem to be picking out

728
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:01,900
-the short and the weak.
-Move along.

729
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:04,650
Turn around.

730
00:39:05,630 --> 00:39:07,000
Short points to you...

731
00:39:07,280 --> 00:39:08,080
Take him away.

732
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:09,840
And weak points to me.

733
00:39:11,260 --> 00:39:12,060
Take him away.

734
00:39:15,670 --> 00:39:16,480
So Xiahou Bo...

735
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:17,070
Take this one away too.

736
00:39:17,070 --> 00:39:19,070
Still hasn't given up on finding us.

737
00:39:21,230 --> 00:39:22,880
Luckily, our elite soldiers with guns

738
00:39:22,880 --> 00:39:24,440
-are all tall and strong.
-Take him away.

739
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:27,700
They shouldn't fall within
the range of their inspection.

740
00:39:28,110 --> 00:39:29,110
Is there anything on our carriage

741
00:39:29,110 --> 00:39:30,570
that could cause trouble?

742
00:39:31,200 --> 00:39:33,400
All the weapons have been distributed.

743
00:39:33,550 --> 00:39:34,110
Take him away.

744
00:39:34,110 --> 00:39:35,000
There's some spare gunpowder

745
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:36,660
hidden underneath the grain.

746
00:39:36,840 --> 00:39:38,710
But if they conduct a deliberate search,

747
00:39:38,710 --> 00:39:40,280
there's still a risk of it
being discovered.

748
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:40,940
This is bad.

749
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:44,680
There's squad heading this way.

750
00:39:44,920 --> 00:39:47,920
-They might want to search our carriage.
-Move along.

751
00:39:49,150 --> 00:39:49,880
Turn around.

752
00:39:53,320 --> 00:39:54,280
We can't wait for Bai anymore.

753
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:55,000
Let's make our move.

754
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:55,460
Hold on.

755
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:57,440
I have an idea.
